<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Meran on 11-21-2000 01:27 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">EQ is a very unusual game in that it is still supported, and essentially still being developed.  They have tried to avoid making changes that would cause a shift in requirements for a long time.

There have been small upgrades here and there, but a lot that has not been done due to system constraints.  And a lot of that is what people have asked for.  As such it is not expected.

If you are willing to pay your $10 a month to play, you still have to realize that sooner or later, like buying a new game, your system will not meet spec.

If all you need is more memory and another video card, then you are in luck.  Most of the new games today will not run on something that has trouble with the "new" EQ, even with additional RAM and a better video card.

As such, I would encourage you to get that extra RAM and new video card.  Or even a new computer.  64MB can be as low as $40 and 128MB as low as $70.  Not too bad.

But it all depends on your final view.  Are you a gamer?  If so, it will happen eventually anyway!

For good memory prices (and guarantees) check out:
 [URL=http://www.crucial.com/index.asp]http://www.crucial.com/index.asp[/URL] 

And FYI, I have a computer with 192MB RAM and 4MB video RAM (when they want 8) that runs fine, though a bit sluggish sometimes.</TEXTAREA>
